## Analysis

The RPM build failed because the spec file iterates over all available Python flavors and attempts to use `/usr/bin/python3.11`, which does not exist in this Tumbleweed build environment (only Python 3.13 is installed). This causes a "No such file or directory" error during the `%build` phase when running `pip wheel`.

**Root cause:** The spec file tries to build for Python 3.11, but that version isn't available in the current build environment.

**Fix:** Add a skip directive at the top of the spec file (below the copyright header) to skip the unsupported Python 3.11 flavor:


This will prevent the build system from attempting to build for Python 3.11, allowing only the available Python 3.13 flavor to be built successfully.